---
title: Integer field
---
The `integer` field is used to store a number.

You can optionally specify a range with `validation.min` and `validation.max`.

## Usage example

```typescript
age: fields.integer({
  label: 'Age',
  description: "The person's age",
  validation: {
    min: 0,
    max: 120
  }
})
```

## Type signature

```typescript
integer({
  label: string;
  defaultValue?: number;
  validation?: {
    isRequired?: IsRequired;
    min: number;
    max: number;
  };
}
```
